We iterate through the string character by character. For each character, we update the count of absences and consecutive late days. If the consecutive late days exceed 3, we immediately return false, as the student has been late for 3 or more consecutive days. Finally, we check if the number of absences is less than or equal to 2 and return true if the condition is satisfied. This solution has a time complexity of O(n) and a space complexity of O(1), making it efficient for large strings.

